The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 A 10-member delegation comprising representatives of the International Cricket Council and the 2011 ODI World Cup sponsors visited Eden Gardens on Monday for a routine inspection of the venue. The delegation expressed satisfaction with the renovation work in progress. What we wanted to see was how the spectator experience could be enhanced.       
	The progress, as of now, is satisfactory, ICC tournament coordinator Dhiraj Malhotra said. He also added that ICC pitch consultant Andy Atkinson was happy with the 22-yard strip at Eden.          
	 Birbhum beat BTA 38-7 in the Concast 27th Junior State Basketball Championship on Monday.      
